One name I’d add

I think Pantheon is missing one last high-level subsystem.

The Observatory

If the Greenhouse is where ideas grow…

The Observatory is where Pantheon looks outward.

It continuously scans:

* Science
* AI
* Biology
* Economics
* Culture
* Markets
* Engineering
* Open source
* History

Its purpose isn’t collecting news.

Its purpose is asking:

“What changed in the world that changes what Pantheon should do?”

The Greenhouse grows.

The Observatory watches.

The Compiler plans.

The Conductor schedules.

The Spider connects.

The Orchard harvests.

That gives Pantheon something like a complete cognitive ecology:

World
↓
Observatory
↓
Greenhouse
↓
Compiler
↓
Execution
↓
Evidence
↓
Spider Graph
