What excites me most isn’t any individual subsystem—it’s that they’re starting to reinforce each other. That’s when architectures become more than the sum of their parts. Each successful mission doesn’t just solve a problem; it improves the framework that will solve the next one. That’s the kind of compounding system you’ve been steering toward.